Title: 
    MISSION IMPOSSIBLE:
    L.O.V.E. PROTOCOL
Draft Date: 3/5/2026

# Night 1
## Act 1

INT. IMF SAFEHOUSE

A simple room. A table with a tablet and an open laptop. 2 chairs. Some crates labeled IMF.
Random tech gear sitting on top of the crates - laptops, wires, binoculars, etc.
BENJY is sitting at the laptop typing rapidly. He has an earpiece and is talking to someone offstage.

BENJY
(into earpiece)
No, no, no, you can't just route it through any other channel! That's not how secure transmission works!
(pause)
Yes, I know you THINK it's faster. That's the problem!
(pause)
No! You can't just override the protocols!
(pause)
Then why didn't you try the backup channel?
(pause)
No, that was the coffee machine's WiFi!

The door bursts open. ETHAN and ILSA enter quickly.
Ilsa looks irritated and fired up.

ILSA
Tell him he's wrong.

BENJY
I'm never wrong.

ILSA
You routed the signal through the wrong channel!

BENJY
That was the only channel available!

ILSA
Because you locked me out of the other three!

BENJY
For security reasons!

ILSA
You locked me out!

BENJY
Exactly!

ETHAN
Alright! Time out.

They keep arguing over him.

ILSA
He compromised the mission!

BENJY
You ignored the plan!

ILSA
The plan was flawed!

BENJY
The plan was perfect!

ETHAN
HEY!

They both stop.

ETHAN
We're on the same team, remember?
(pause)
Did we at least get the data?

BENJY
Of course we got the data.
(proudly)
I got the data.

ILSA
WE got the data.

BENJY
Mostly me.

ILSA
Barely you.

BENJY
Technically—

ETHAN
Benjy.

Benjy stops talking.

ETHAN
Have you had time to analyze it?

BENJY
Oh yeah.
(excited)
You're going to love this.
(gestures to the tablet)
HQ already sent the next mission.
(points to tablet)
Right there.

ETHAN picks up the tablet.
Ethan taps the tablet. Lights dim slightly. Everyone turns toward the screen as the mission briefing video begins.

MISSION BRIEFING - FEMALE (V.O.)
Facial recognition complete.

MISSION BRIEFING - MALE (V.O.)
Ethan, recent intelligence gathered by your team has confirmed the existence of a mysterious device known only as “The Light.”
Little is known about the device's exact capabilities. However, intercepted communications suggest that many powerful groups are actively searching for it.
Rumors surrounding The Light include the ability to grant immense power, unimaginable wealth, or even eternal life.
While these claims remain unverified, what is certain is that the device is valuable enough that others are willing to take extreme risks to obtain it.
The device is believed to have been designed by a brilliant but unidentified figure known only as “The Architect.”
At this time, the Architect's identity and motives remain unknown.
Your mission is to locate The Light and secure it before hostile organizations can reach it first.
Due to the potential global consequences surrounding this device, strict operational protocol must be followed.
This mission will require precision, coordination, and discipline.
All agents are expected to follow established procedures and execute their roles exactly as assigned.
Deviation from mission protocol increases the likelihood of failure.
Remember:
Successful operations depend on trust in your team, respect for the chain of command, and obedience to the instructions of the designated team leader.
For this mission, Ethan has command authority.
All team members are to follow his instructions without deviation unless directed otherwise by IMF Command.
As always, if any members of your team are caught or killed, the secretary will disavow any knowledge of your actions. This message will self-destruct in five seconds. Good luck, Ethan.

Video ends. Lights return to normal.
The door opens and JEREMY enters, carrying a tactical backpack and two juice boxes.

BENJY
Well… that sounded ominous.

ILSA
It sounded clear.

BENJY
Clear and ominous.

JEREMY
Hey guys! Sorry I'm late. I got turned around. Who wants fruit punch?

As he says this, Benjy and Ilsa both turn in surprise. Ethan shows no reaction.

ETHAN
Benjy, Ilsa, this is Jeremy Hunt. He's Marine Special Forces — reconnaissance and counter-intelligence. Top of his class in tactical operations, expert in field surveillance and infiltration, and one of the fastest mission assessment analysts the Marines have ever produced. When things get complicated, he's the guy they'd send in to figure it out. Now he works for the IMF.

JEREMY
(beaming)
And I make an excellent grilled cheese.
(offers a juice box to Ilsa)
Fruit punch?

ILSA
(stares at it)
No. 

JEREMY
So, the instructions are: find mysterious device, secure it, and don't get caught. Got it.

ILSA
That's a very casual summary of a very serious mission.

JEREMY
Relax. I work best under pressure.

BENJY
You don't look like you're under pressure.

JEREMY
A professional never does.

ETHAN
The important part of that briefing wasn't the rumors about the device.
It was the reminder.
Missions like this only work if everyone follows the plan.

JEREMY
Oh, absolutely! 100%. Protocol. Procedures. Structure.
Love all that.
Very exciting stuff.

ILSA
You sound a little *too* thrilled.

JEREMY
I'm just eager! I mean, sometimes you have to improvise to help the team, right? You know, anticipating needs before they happen? Like the juice boxes.

Ilsa raises an eyebrow.

ILSA
That attitude is exactly how missions fall apart.

BENJY
Yeah. The last time someone anticipated my needs and treated the plan like a suggestion, I spent three hours hanging upside down from a ceiling.

ILSA
You're bringing that up again?!

JEREMY
Did it work?

BENJY
Well, yes, but that's not the point…

JEREMY
See? Innovation.

ETHAN
Jeremy.
(Jeremy snaps to attention.)
The reason we follow instructions is because each of us individually don't always see the whole picture. We have to trust those in authority over us to give us the best information and the best plan.

JEREMY
Got it. Obey the plan. Trust HQ. No improvising.

Ilsa and Benjy exchange a look.

ETHAN
Alright.
Benjy, gather everything we have on The Architect.
Ilsa, start mapping possible locations where this device could be hidden.
Jeremy—
(Jeremy salutes awkwardly.)
Stay ready. We'll brief the full operation once we have more intel.

JEREMY
Copy that.
I'll be… extremely ready.

BENJY
That confidence is either comforting or terrifying.
I haven't decided which.

They begin gathering around the table reviewing maps and data.

===

## Act 2

INT. SERVER VAULT - NIGHT

A dimly lit, high-security server room. Racks of blinking equipment hum quietly.
At the center of the room sits a TERMINAL on a pedestal.
The floor between the entrance and the terminal is divided into square panels.
Only one path across the floor is safe.
Jeremy stands at the entrance to the grid, studying the floor.

In his ear, the team speaks over comms.

BENJY (V.O.)
Alright Jeremy, you should be looking at a grid of floor panels.

JEREMY
I see it.

BENJY (V.O.)
Each square is pressure sensitive. Step on the wrong one and the vault triggers a security protocol.

JEREMY
And the Light relocates. Got it.

ETHAN (V.O.)
Jeremy, I have the path on my tablet. Follow my instructions exactly.

JEREMY
Copy that.

BENJY (V.O.)
And Jeremy?

JEREMY
Yeah?

BENJY (V.O.)
Try not to step on the wrong ones.

JEREMY
Comforting.

ETHAN (V.O.)
Alright. First step — forward two squares.

Jeremy moves carefully. His steps are precise and controlled.

ETHAN (V.O.)
Now one to your left.

Jeremy steps.

ETHAN (V.O.)
Forward one.

JEREMY
You know, this would be a lot easier if I had the tablet.

BENJY (V.O.)
We went over that already. The tablet has to be directly connected to the mainframe.

ETHAN (V.O.)
Jeremy, stay focused. Next step forward.

Jeremy steps again.

INT. BUILDING LOBBY - SAME TIME

[[seems like she needs more to do]]ILSA stands near the entrance, keeping watch.

ILSA
Lobby's still quiet.

INT. SERVER VAULT - CONTINUOUS

Jeremy reaches the middle of the grid.
Suddenly a faint CLICK is heard.

JEREMY
Uh... Ethan?

ETHAN (V.O.)
I see it.

BENJY (V.O.)
That's not good.

JEREMY
Let me guess.

BENJY (V.O.)
Security pattern just changed.

ETHAN (V.O.)
That wasn't supposed to happen yet.

BENJY (V.O.)
They must have accelerated the vault cycle.

ETHAN (V.O.)
Benjy, can you delay it?

BENJY (V.O.)
I'm trying.

Jeremy studies the floor ahead of him.

ETHAN (V.O.)
Alright Jeremy. Hold position.

JEREMY
Holding.

ETHAN (V.O.)
Benjy almost has it, just give him a few more seconds!

Jeremy studies the floor again.
He spots the final square near the terminal.
A long gap between where he stands and the last safe panel.

JEREMY
Ethan… I'm looking at the terminal from here.

ETHAN (V.O.)
Stay where you are.

JEREMY
If I jump the last panel I can clear the grid.

ETHAN (V.O.)
Negative.

BENJY (V.O.)
Almost there… almost there…

Jeremy crouches slightly, calculating the distance.

ETHAN (V.O.)
Jeremy, if you miss at all the Light will be moved and we'll have nothing.

BENJY (V.O.)
Just a few more seconds!

JEREMY
We're out of time. I can help!
(beat)
I'm going for it.

ETHAN (V.O.)
No, wait!

Jeremy leaps across the grid.
His boot lands on the final square.
For a split second his heel presses down on the wrong panel.[[need to make clear that he's stepping on the wrong one]]
But—
Nothing happens.
No alarms.
No lights.
Jeremy smirks slightly.

JEREMY
Told you.

He walks to the terminal and begins typing.

ETHAN (V.O.)
What's happening?

BENJY (V.O.)
I've got it!

JEREMY
I'm already here. Plugging in now.
(he inserts the secure drive)
Starting the download.
(pause)
It's running.

BENJY (V.O.)
Wait something is wrong.

ETHAN (V.O.)
What?

JEREMY
20%.

BENJY (V.O.)
Someone else is in the system.

ILSA
What? Who?

BENJY (V.O.)
I don't know! I don't know! Jeremy what's happening?

JEREMY
It's at 32% but the bar stopped moving.

ILSA (V.O.)
We have company.

ETHAN (V.O.)
Benjy, what's going on?

BENJY (V.O.)
Hang on...
(beat)
There it is!
The alarm was triggered.

ETHAN (V.O.)
Which alarm?

BENJY (V.O.)
The floor alarm! The one we were supposed to avoid by following directions!
(pause-keyboard sounds)
The Light is being moved.

Jeremy stares at the screen as warning messages appear.

JEREMY
Uh... I've got errors coming up on the screen now.

The download bar suddenly disappears.

BENJY (V.O.)
The server is relocating The Light!

ETHAN (V.O.)
Jeremy, pull the drive and get out of there.
This mission is over.

Jeremy yanks the drive from the terminal.

JEREMY
Copy.

He moves quickly across the room and exits.

INT. BUILDING LOBBY - SAME TIME

Ilsa steps away from the window.

ILSA
I'm clear. Moving out.

TRANSITION TO:

INT. IMF SAFEHOUSE - LATER

The team gathers around the main table.
Tension fills the room.
Benjy studies the laptop.

BENJY
It's gone.

Jeremy stands quietly.

ETHAN
Walk me through it.

JEREMY
The floor pattern changed halfway through.

BENJY
Which is why we needed the delay.

JEREMY
I had a clear shot to the final square. I took it.

BENJY
And triggered the alarm.

Jeremy exhales.

JEREMY
It didn't trigger immediately.

BENJY
No.
(beat)
It waited until the transfer started.

ETHAN
Which means the vault recorded the wrong step... and moved the Light the moment we accessed the system.

Silence.

ETHAN (CONT'D)
Jeremy... your jump almost worked.

Jeremy looks up, surprised.

ETHAN (CONT'D)
But the mission wasn't yours to redesign.
(beat)
We had a plan.
We had instructions.
And every part of that mission depended on everyone following them exactly.

Jeremy nods slowly.

ETHAN (CONT'D)
When we start deciding our own way is better... that's when things fall apart.
(beat)
Tonight, we lost the Light.

===

# Night 2

## Act 1

INT. IMF SAFEHOUSE - NIGHT

The team gathers around the central table. A laptop and tablet sit open, displaying maps, code, and fragments of data.
Benjy types furiously on the laptop. ILSA stands nearby, arms crossed, watching the screen.
Ethan studies the tablet.
Jeremy leans casually against a crate.

BENJY
I'm telling you, the vault security didn't just move the program randomly. There's a relocation pattern.

ILSA
And I'm telling you that pattern doesn't matter if we can't predict where it's going next.

BENJY
Of course it matters. Patterns always matter.

ILSA
Unless the system adapts.

BENJY
It's software, Ilsa. Software follows rules.

ILSA
Not if someone designed it not to.

BENJY
That would be ridiculous.

ILSA
Would it?

JEREMY
This is fascinating. Really. But are we planning the next mission or hosting a debate club?

BENJY
I'm planning the mission.

ILSA
You're guessing.

BENJY
I am not guessing.

ILSA
You literally just said “probably.”

BENJY
That was a strategic “probably.”

JEREMY
(holding up a bag)
Hey guys, I brought tactical trail mix. Anyone want some M&Ms? It helps with tension. I ate all the brown ones already.

ILSA
Not now, Jeremy.

ETHAN
Enough.

They quiet down.

ETHAN (CONT'D)
We lost the Light once. We're not doing that again.

Jeremy nods slightly.

ETHAN (CONT'D)
Benjy, what do we know?

BENJY
The Light relocated immediately after the floor alarm triggered.

He gestures to the screen.

BENJY (CONT'D)
The program moved to another server in the network, but the trail goes cold after that.

ILSA
Meaning someone hid it.

BENJY
Meaning someone knew we were there.

Jeremy straightens a little.

JEREMY
We already knew we weren't the only ones looking for it.

Suddenly the laptop screen flickers.
The lights on the equipment blink.
BENJY freezes.

BENJY
...that's not good.

ILSA
What did you do?

BENJY
I didn't do anything!

The screen goes dark.
Then a new message appears.
A distorted voice fills the room.

THE NULL (V.O.)
You were closer than I expected.

The team looks up at the screen.

THE NULL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
That usually makes failure harder to accept.

BENJY
Someone's in our system.

ILSA
Obviously.

ETHAN steps forward.

ETHAN
Who are you?

THE NULL (V.O.)
A witness.
If you need a name… call me the Null.

JEREMY
(scoffing)
Subtle.

THE NULL (V.O.)
Not really.
Subtle would have been letting you believe the vault was your only mistake.

BENJY
You triggered the relocation.

Jeremy stiffens slightly.

THE NULL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
I accelerated it.
You triggered it.
There is a difference.

THE NULL (V.O.)
You were told to hold position.
You jumped.
You nearly succeeded.
That is what makes disobedience so useful.
It feels wise right up until everything falls apart.

ETHAN
Why are you contacting us?

THE NULL (V.O.)
Because I wanted to see whether the failure had done its work.

Benjy begins typing rapidly.
Ilsa leans over the keyboard.

ILSA
Move.

BENJY
I'm tracing him.

ILSA
Not on that port.

BENJY
Don't start.

ILSA
Then stop missing relays.

She reaches in and types something.
BENJY watches, annoyed, then keeps going.

THE NULL (V.O.)
There it is.
The blame.
You save me so much time.

BENJY
I'm tracing the signal.
I can find you.

THE NULL (V.O.)
Can you?
Or will she have to correct you again?

ILSA
Keep talking.

THE NULL (V.O.)
Gladly.
Jeremy thinks the plan failed him.
Benjy thinks Jeremy cost him the Light.
Ilsa thinks Benjy's pride keeps making things worse.
And Ethan...
(beat)
Ethan is wondering whether any of you can be trusted with the next move.

The room goes still for a moment.

ETHAN
You're trying to divide us.

THE NULL (V.O.)
Trying?
No.
I'm simply saying out loud what failure already whispered.

JEREMY
You don't know this team.

THE NULL (V.O.)
I know enough.
You are not hard to read.
One ignored instruction, one bruised ego, one argument at the keyboard...
and the mission collapses.

ETHAN
What do you want?

THE NULL (V.O.)
The Light of course.

Benjy slams a key.

BENJY
Almost got him.

ILSA
No, that's a loop. He's feeding us a false trace.

BENJY
What?

THE NULL (V.O.)
Yes.
And you took it immediately.

The screen flickers again.

THE NULL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
That is the trouble with deception.
People usually help it along.

JEREMY
Then I guess we're still in the race.

THE NULL (V.O.)
No, Jeremy.
You're in each other's way.
(pause)
Goodbye, agents.

The screen goes black.
Silence.
BENJY keeps typing.

BENJY
Come on… come on…

He stops.

BENJY (CONT'D)
He's gone.

ETHAN
Did you get anything?

BENJY exhales.

BENJY
Whoever that was masked the signal behind about twelve layers of encryption and bounced it through half the internet.
So technically yes… I traced it.

JEREMY
To where?

BENJY
Everywhere.

ILSA
Meaning nowhere.

BENJY
Exactly.

Jeremy folds his arms.

JEREMY
So he didn't just bait the trace.
He baited us.

ILSA
And he was counting on this exact reaction.

BENJY
Then maybe we should stop giving him one.

Jeremy gives him a look.

JEREMY
Go ahead. Say it.

ETHAN steps forward.

ETHAN
Enough.

The room quiets.

ETHAN (CONT'D)
Listen to yourselves.
He didn't break into our system just to threaten us.
He came here to accuse, deceive, and divide.
And for a minute, we let him.

He looks at Benjy, Ilsa, and Jeremy.

ETHAN (CONT'D)
That ends now.
This mission just changed.
We're not just chasing the Light.
We're up against someone who knows he can't beat a united team, so he'll keep trying to split us apart.

JEREMY
So what do we do?

ETHAN
We close the gaps. And that starts with forgiveness. 
God calls us to forgive each other, especially when we mess up. If we hold onto this bitterness, the Null has already won.

Silence. Benjy avoids looking at Ilsa.
Ilsa crosses her arms.

ILSA
I can work with him. We're professionals. But I'm not ready to let this go.

BENJY
Right. The mission comes first. We'll just... focus on the mission.

ETHAN
Ignoring it isn't fixing it. You can't just 'work together' when there's a wall between you.

JEREMY
(quietly)
He's right, you know.

ILSA
(sharp)
Let's just prep the next phase.

They turn back to the monitors, avoiding each other. The tension is still heavy.

FADE OUT.

===

## Act 2

INT. RESEARCH FACILITY CORRIDOR - NIGHT

A sterile hallway washed in low red security light.
At the far end stands a sealed BIOMETRIC DOOR labeled COMPUTER CORE.
ETHAN kneels beside the scanner, one hand on his earpiece, eyes locked on the door.

Elsewhere in the building, BENJY and ILSA work separate angles over comms.
Somewhere deeper inside, JEREMY moves alone through the facility.

ETHAN
Status.

BENJY (V.O.)
You're at the right door. Palm scanner on the left, keypad on the right?

ETHAN
That's what I'm looking at.

ILSA (V.O.)
Then give me thirty seconds.

BENJY (V.O.)
You wouldn't need thirty seconds if you hadn't ruined the original handprint.

ILSA (V.O.)
I didn't ruin it. Your timing was off, so I adapted.

BENJY (V.O.)
My timing was exact.

ETHAN
Both of you. Focus.

JEREMY (V.O.)
Checkpoint four clear.
The duct maze was disgusting, the laser hall was rude, and I would like that noted in the mission report.

BENJY (V.O.)
Noted.
Keep moving.

ETHAN
Next checkpoint in sixty seconds, Jeremy.

JEREMY (V.O.)
See? I'm checking in.
Personal growth.

ETHAN steps closer to the door.
As he does, the DOOR UNIT slowly pivots out from the back wall, revealing the COMPUTER ROOM on the opposite side to the audience.
Inside: a dark room, a glowing console, and a wall monitor mirroring the computer display.
Ethan cannot see any of it yet.

INT. COMPUTER ROOM - SAME TIME

Above the console, a ceiling panel silently opens.
A FIGURE DRESSED IN BLACK lowers on a cable and lands beside the machine.

INT. RESEARCH FACILITY CORRIDOR - CONTINUOUS

JEREMY (V.O.)
Crossing the west stairwell now. Should hit checkpoint five in twenty.

ETHAN
Report the moment you get there.

JEREMY (V.O.)
Copy that.

INT. COMPUTER ROOM - SAME TIME

The figure plugs a device into the computer.
The wall monitor lights up: ACCESSING ARCHIVE.

INT. RESEARCH FACILITY CORRIDOR - CONTINUOUS

BENJY (V.O.)
Ilsa, send the print.

ILSA (V.O.)
Working on it.

BENJY (V.O.)
That is not the same as sending it.

ILSA (V.O.)
Because unlike you, I prefer accuracy.

BENJY (V.O.)
Unlike you, I prefer the part where the plan still works.

A beat.

ETHAN
Jeremy, checkpoint five.

Silence.

ETHAN (CONT'D)
Jeremy?

BENJY (V.O.)
He's probably still moving.

ETHAN
Jeremy, respond.

Static crackles.

JEREMY (V.O.)
(out of breath)
Still here.
Took a detour around a patrol.
I'm at checkpoint fi-

A sudden struggle erupts over comms.
A sharp grunt. A metallic crash.
Then heavy static.

JEREMY (V.O.) (CONT'D)
Ethan-

The channel cuts out.

ETHAN
Jeremy? Jeremy!

No answer.

INT. COMPUTER ROOM - SAME TIME

The transfer bar climbs: 18%... 31%.

INT. RESEARCH FACILITY CORRIDOR - CONTINUOUS

ILSA (V.O.)
I heard it.

BENJY (V.O.)
So did I.

ETHAN
Ilsa, where are you?

ILSA (V.O.)
One corridor over from the security office.

ETHAN
Get me the print, then find Jeremy.
Benjy, get this door open now.

BENJY (V.O.)
Trying.

A chime hits Ethan's phone.

BENJY (V.O.) (CONT'D)
You should have the file.

Ethan raises the phone to the scanner.
The reader flashes red.

ETHAN
No good.

BENJY (V.O.)
What?
No, no, no, that should have taken.

ILSA (V.O.)
Because the system wants a full print, not your fake approval packet.

BENJY (V.O.)
My fake approval packet is the only reason this has any chance of working!

ILSA (V.O.)
If you had trusted my route, I would've had the real print ten minutes ago.

BENJY (V.O.)
If you had followed my route, the first print wouldn't be useless!

ETHAN
Enough!

He slaps the phone down against his leg, forcing calm.

ETHAN (CONT'D)
We do not have time for this.
Ilsa, send it again.
Benjy, when it comes through, make it work.

INT. COMPUTER ROOM - SAME TIME

The wall monitor climbs: 46%... 57%.

INT. RESEARCH FACILITY CORRIDOR - CONTINUOUS

Jeremy's channel stays dead.

ETHAN
Jeremy, report.

Only static.

ILSA (V.O.)
Sending a fresh scan now.

BENJY (V.O.)
Wait - don't send while I'm rewriting the handshake-

The file arrives.

BENJY (V.O.) (CONT'D)
Too late.

ILSA (V.O.)
Then rewrite faster.

BENJY (V.O.)
That is not how coding works!

ETHAN closes his eyes for half a second.

ETHAN
Benjy.

BENJY (V.O.)
Right.
Working.

A tense beat.
Ethan watches the corridor behind him, then the locked door.

Another chime.

ETHAN
Got it.
(raises phone to scanner)
Great, Ilsa. Now go find Jeremy.

ILSA (V.O.)
On it.

The scanner reads.
Red light.

ETHAN
Benjy, it's not working.

INT. COMPUTER ROOM - SAME TIME

The figure in black reaches 79% and types another command.

INT. RESEARCH FACILITY CORRIDOR - CONTINUOUS

BENJY (V.O.)
Ok, hold on, hold on!
(keyboard sounds)
Ok, try it now!

Ethan scans again.
Green light.
A click from the biometric lock.

ETHAN
It worked.
There's a password too.

BENJY (V.O.)
Intel didn't say anything about a password!
Ok hang on.
I'm already in this, shouldn't be too difficult.

INT. COMPUTER ROOM - SAME TIME

The figure ejects the device and disconnects it.
The transfer completes.
On the screen, one line appears: NULL ACCESS CONFIRMED.

The figure starts ascending toward the ceiling.

INT. RESEARCH FACILITY CORRIDOR - CONTINUOUS

ETHAN waits, jaw tight.

ETHAN
Benjy.

BENJY (V.O.)
Almost there...
almost there...
Ok, the password is 7x77.

Ethan types the code.
The door unlocks.

INT. COMPUTER ROOM - CONTINUOUS

Ethan bursts into the room just as the ceiling panel slides shut above him.
A cable swings slightly in the air.

He crosses to the console and types.
His face falls.

ETHAN
(into comms)
Someone just wiped the files.

BENJY (V.O.)
What?

Ethan studies the access log.

ON THE SCREEN:
LAST USER: NULL

ETHAN
He left his signature.
It was the Null.

He looks up at the seam in the ceiling.

ETHAN (CONT'D)
He came in from above.

ILSA (V.O.)
Ethan...

She sounds different now. Breathless.

ETHAN
Report.

ILSA (V.O.)
I found checkpoint five.
Jeremy isn't here.
There's no sign of him.

Silence.

BENJY (V.O.)
Jeremy, if you can hear us, answer.

Nothing.
ETHAN stares at the blank screen.

TRANSITION TO:

INT. IMF SAFEHOUSE - LATER

The room is quieter than usual.
No one leans against the wall. No one jokes from the corner.
Jeremy's absence hangs over the whole space.

Benjy sits at the laptop, exhausted.
Ilsa stands across from him, tense and still.
Ethan remains at the head of the table.

BENJY
I pulled everything I could from the terminal.
The Null got there first, took the archive, and wiped the system before Ethan got through the door.

ILSA
And Jeremy's tracker went dark at checkpoint five.
No cameras. No usable prints. Nothing.

BENJY looks down.

BENJY
So we lost the Light.
Again.

No one answers.

ETHAN
The Null didn't beat us at that door.
He beat us before I ever touched the scanner.
He got us looking at each other like the enemy.

Benjy and Ilsa both know he's right.

ETHAN (CONT'D)
I told you earlier that we needed to forgive each other, and you thought you could just push through it safely. Look where that got us.
We can't do this on our own strength. We're too stubborn. We need to rely on God's grace. He forgave us when we didn't deserve it, and He's asking us to do the same for each other.
Not for the mission. For each other.

A long beat. The weight of Ethan's words, and Jeremy's absence, settles on them.

BENJY
(quietly)
Lord, help me let this go.
(turns to Ilsa)
Ilsa... I was so busy proving my plan was better that I stopped listening. I cared more about being right than helping you. It was pride, and it cost us Jeremy. I'm sorry.

ILSA meets his eyes.

ILSA
(voice shaking slightly)
I changed the handprint plan because I thought I could fix it myself.
I didn't tell anyone until it was already broken.
(beat)
I kept fighting you because I didn't want to admit I was wrong. I'm sorry too.

BENJY
I know we can't fix tonight. But... can you forgive me?

Ilsa softens. The wall finally breaks.

ILSA
Yes. I forgive you.
(beat)
Can you forgive me?

BENJY
Yeah.
I can.

ETHAN lets the silence settle.

ETHAN
Good.
When we rely on God to heal those fractures, the Null loses his greatest weapon against us.

He looks at the empty place where Jeremy would usually stand.

ETHAN (CONT'D)
Tonight he took the Light.
And he took Jeremy.

The weight of that lands.

ETHAN (CONT'D)
We cannot change tonight by blaming each other.
But we can decide what kind of team we are when the next mission starts.

ILSA
A better one.

BENJY
And this time, when someone says, "Focus," I will assume they mean all of us.

Ethan gives the faintest nod.

ETHAN
Until we know otherwise, Jeremy is alive.
And we are bringing him home.

FADE OUT.

===

# Night 3

## Act 1

INT. IMF SAFEHOUSE - NIGHT

Only moments later.
The room looks the same, but the energy is completely different.
Benjy is still at the laptop, pulling up whatever traces he can.
Ilsa paces near the table.
Ethan stands still, staring at the empty place where Jeremy should be.

BENJY
I really hate saying this out loud...
(beat)
this guy is good.

ILSA
He got in and out of a sealed computer room, stole the Light, and left almost nothing behind.

ETHAN
He's more than a hacker.
He had to know the building, the timing, the entry point, and our response window.
Whoever the Null is, he's smart enough to break a system and skilled enough to move through it.

BENJY
Which is an extremely dangerous combination.

ILSA stops pacing.

ILSA
And now he has the Light.

ETHAN turns toward the table.
Something catches his eye.

A TABLET sits beside the laptop.
Same model as before.

ETHAN
Benjy.
Was that here before?

Benjy looks up.

BENJY
No.

ILSA
I didn't bring it.

BENJY
Please tell me HQ has not started delivering updates by mysterious surprise tablet.

Ethan picks it up carefully.
The screen is black.

ETHAN
Only one way to find out.

He taps the screen.
Lights dim slightly.

MISSION BRIEFING - FEMALE (V.O.)
Facial recognition complete. Hello Ethan.

BENJY
That was a lot less comforting this time.

The screen brightens.
At first, it looks and sounds exactly like a standard IMF message.

MISSION BRIEFING - MALE (V.O.)
Your team failed to secure the Light. This is unacceptable.
You were given a clear objective, and you failed to complete it.
A hostile party took the asset before your team could secure it.
That failure has compromised the mission and escalated the threat.
(pause)
I'm honestly surprised how easy it was to break your team completely.

BENJY
(interrupting)
That's awefully personal for a mission briefing.

MISSION BRIEFING - MALE (V.O.) (CONT'D)
You'll need to work together much better than that if you ever want to see your friend Jeremy again.

Ilsa and Benjy exchange a quick look.

ILSA
What is this? Where did this message come from?

Benjy moves toward the laptop and starts typing, but there is no response from the message.

MISSION BRIEFING - MALE (V.O.) (CONT'D)
Even though you lost the Light, your mission is not over.
Possession of the Light does not mean control of it.
The Light is encrypted. Only someone with the access code can unlock it.

The screen flickers.
The lights dim.
The screen and voice changes to the NULL.

THE NULL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
And you are going to find it for me.

BENJY
It's the Null.

ILSA
He has the Light AND Jeremy.

THE NULL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
Before you start imagining a way out of this.
The last time you failed, you lost the Light.
This time, you'll lose a friend.

Ethan's expression hardens.

THE NULL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
Bring me the code, and Jeremy goes free.
Refuse me, delay me, or attempt anything creative...
and you will not see your friend again.

Benjy stops typing for just a second.

THE NULL (V.O.) (CONT'D)
Do not comfort yourselves with the thought that I am bluffing.
You have already seen how quickly one wrong move can cost you.
Your mission, whether you choose to accept it or not, is to recover my code.
Try not to fail this mission the way you failed the last two.
I think you'll find you have all you need.

The screen goes black.
Lights return to normal.

No one speaks for a beat.

BENJY
I hate him.

ILSA
How do we know he's not lying?
We didn't see Jeremy.
We didn't hear him.

ETHAN
We don't. But what choice do we have?

BENJY
He wasn't kidding about the code.

ILSA
Meaning?

BENJY
Meaning the Light is locked tight.
Like stealing a safe without the combination.
He can carry it around all he wants, but he still can't get what's inside.

ILSA
And if we get the code for him, we hand him exactly what he needs.

BENJY
Pretty much, yes.

ILSA
Then why would we help him?

ETHAN
We don't help him.
We move before he does.

Ilsa looks at him.

ETHAN (CONT'D)
If Jeremy is with him, we bring Jeremy home.
If the code is real, we secure it before the Null can use it.

BENJY
So we're accepting a mission from the guy who stole our mission.

ETHAN
We're taking back control of it.

ILSA
And if we find the Null first?

Ethan looks at both of them.

ETHAN
Then we stop him.
But we are not doing this out of anger or revenge.
He wants us to hate him. He's counting on it. But doing the impossible—choosing to love our enemy—is the only way we break his trap.

That lands.

BENJY
Where do we even start?

ETHAN
This tablet. I doubt we'll find much, but it's the only lead we have.
He touched it, he loaded the message onto it, and he left it here.
Maybe we can find something that leads us to him.

ILSA
What about the decryption code?

BENJY
Ya, wait, what did he mean by, "You have all you need"?

Benjy taps away on the tablet for a few moments.

BENJY
Look at this, Ethan.

ETHAN
Is that...?
That's the Light.

ILSA looks too.

ILSA
Well, now we know he was telling the truth. Let's get this thing back to HQ.

ETHAN
No, like you said. Now we know he was telling the truth. 
The only reason he would freely give us the Light is if he really has Jeremy.

BENJY
So we really don't have any choice.

ETHAN
Let's get to work.

FADE OUT.

## Act 2

INT. DECRYPTION CORE - NIGHT

A high-tech corridor bathed in blue light. The path forward is blocked by a dense grid of glowing red LASERS. 
At the far end of the corridor sits the central TERMINAL—the Decryption Core.

ETHAN stands at the edge of the laser grid. He taps his earpiece.

ETHAN
I'm at the grid. It's active.

BENJY (V.O.)
I see it. The system is heavily fortified. Ilsa, are you tied into the secondary mainframe?

ILSA (V.O.)
Tied in and holding. Awaiting your mark, Benjy.

BENJY (V.O.)
Okay. The only way through is if Ilsa and I drop the laser modules in sequence. We have a three-second window for each section before the system resets.

ETHAN
Just like the floor grid. Only this time, we do it together. Tell me when.

BENJY (V.O.)
Ilsa, drop the lower grid in 3... 2... 1... Mark.

ILSA (V.O.)
Lower grid down. Go, Ethan!

Ethan steps forward, ducking under a high laser.

BENJY (V.O.)
Resetting in 2... 1... Taking control of the middle grid. Dropping now!

Ethan steps precisely through the opening.

ETHAN
I'm through the middle. One more section.

ILSA (V.O.)
I've got the final matrix. Dropping it... now!

Ethan makes one final deliberate move and clears the grid entirely. 
The lasers behind him immediately hum back to life.

ETHAN
I'm clear. I'm at the terminal. Excellent work, you two.

BENJY (V.O.)
See what happens when nobody goes rogue? I'm initiating the download to the secure drive now.

ILSA (V.O.)
Wait. Benjy... the security protocols in my wing just engaged.

BENJY (V.O.)
What? No, that's impossible, I disabled those-- Wait. My blast doors just triggered.

ETHAN
Benjy? Ilsa? What's happening?

Over comms, SIRENS blare.

ILSA (V.O.)
Someone's overriding the system! Oxygen is venting!

BENJY (V.O.)
It's the Null! He locked us in! Ethan, you have to--

Static. The comms go dead.

ETHAN
Benjy! Ilsa!

The lights in the Decryption Core suddenly shut off. 
A single spotlight illuminates the center of the room.

THE NULL steps out from the shadows, dressed entirely in black, wearing a featureless mask.

THE NULL
They are out of time, Ethan.

Ethan slowly turns around to face him.

ETHAN
Let them go. You have what you want.

THE NULL
Not yet. I need the code. And now I have the leverage to ensure you give it to me. Hand over the drive, or your friends won't make it out of those rooms.

Ethan stares at him. He reaches into his jacket, pulls out a sleek metallic DRIVE, and holds it out.

ETHAN
You put a lot of work into this. The hacking, the infiltration...

The Null reaches out and takes the drive.

THE NULL
It was remarkably easy.

ETHAN
I know. 
(beat)
This isn't what you think it is... Jeremy.

The Null freezes.
Slowly, he reaches up and pulls off the mask.
It is JEREMY. No longer goofy. His expression is cold and arrogant.

JEREMY
How did you know?

ETHAN
The tablet in the safehouse. No one could have planted that unless they already had access. We were supposed to be searching for a ghost, but the real threat was standing right next to us.

JEREMY
(smirks)
And yet, you still walked right into my trap. You were so desperate to save your team that you handed over the only thing that matters.

ETHAN
I didn't hand it over because I was trapped. I handed it to you because I wanted to give you a chance.

Jeremy looks confused.

ETHAN (CONT'D)
Jeremy, you don't have to do this. You've spent this whole time running from protocol, trying to prove you're smarter than everyone else, tearing this team apart just to serve yourself. But it's only going to leave you empty and alone.

JEREMY
Save the lecture, Ethan. I beat you.

ETHAN
You didn't. God commands us to love our enemies. To offer grace when they deserve punishment. You betrayed us. You hurt this team. But I forgive you. We forgive you. Put the drive down, and come back with us.

Jeremy stares at Ethan. For a moment, his arrogant exterior slips. He looks down at the drive.
But then his pride returns. His expression hardens.

JEREMY
I don't need your grace. And I don't need this team.

Jeremy turns and sprints toward the exit.

He bursts through the doorway--
And runs directly into BENJY and ILSA.
They stand perfectly fine, arms crossed.

Jeremy skids to a halt, shocked.

BENJY
Going somewhere?

ILSA
We prefer to be told when we're leaving the team.

JEREMY
How-- I locked you in! The comms...

ETHAN steps up behind Jeremy.

ETHAN
The comms were faked. We knew you were listening. When you realize the enemy's game plan, you don't fight each other. You work together to subvert it.

Benjy steps forward and plucks the drive from Jeremy's hand.

BENJY
Also... you shouldn't have gloated so much.
(holds up the drive)
This is my mixtape. 

Ilsa grabs Jeremy by the arms, securing him.

JEREMY
You set me up.

ETHAN
We gave you a choice. You made the wrong one.

Ethan turns back to the Decryption Terminal. He types briskly.

ILSA
So, if that was a fake... how do we actually decrypt the Light?

ETHAN
The Architect didn't leave a standard password. The instructions required faith.

Ethan types a final sequence on the keyboard.

COMPUTER VOICE (V.O.)
Passcode accepted. Matthew 5:44. Decryption complete. The Light is unlocked.

The terminal screen glows brightly, casting a warm, golden light across the room.

BENJY
Is it... a weapon?

ETHAN
No. It's the Word of God. The greatest set of instructions ever given. It doesn't tell us how to be perfect agents, or how to get rich, or how to live forever on earth. It tells us how to depend on God when we face impossible situations.

Ethan turns to look at the team.

ETHAN (CONT'D)
Because living the life God calls us to—obeying Him, forgiving those who hurt us, and loving our enemies—is impossible to do on our own. We can only do it with Jesus.

The golden light washes over the team. Even Jeremy looks humbled, staring silently at the source of The Light.

ETHAN (CONT'D)
Mission accomplished. Let's go home.

FADE OUT.

